Usage: create_interposer_route_block [-help] -cell <string> -dir <string>
                                     -inst <string> [{-box {x1 y1 x2 y2} | -polygon {x1 y1 x2 y2 ...} | -rects {{lx1 ly1 ux1 uy1} {lx2 ly2 ux2 uy2}...}}]

-help                          # Prints out the command usage
-box {x1 y1 x2 y2}             # specifies the master block's bounding box
                               # (box, optional)
-cell <string>                 # specifies the master cell name
                               # (string, required)
-dir <string>                  # specifies the directory name that will contain
                               # the partition information and files
                               # (string, required)
-inst <string>                 # specifies the master block name
                               # (string, required)
-polygon {x1 y1 x2 y2 ...}     # specifies the master block's corner
                               # coordinates {{x1 y1} {x2 y2}...}
                               # (polygon, optional)
-rects {{lx1 ly1 ux1 uy1} {lx2 ly2 ux2 uy2}...}
                               # specifies the master block's box list {{lx1
                               # ly1 ux1 uy1} {lx2 ly2 ux2 uy2}...}
                               # (box_list, optional)